            <abstract>
              <p>A shorter version of the supplicative table prayer (also described in catalogues as prayer
                  over bread and wine of the Eucharist), <ref type="work" corresp="https://betamasaheft.eu/LIT5069Prayer">Saʾalnāka maḥari saʾalnāka faṭāri</ref>,
                                      cp. <bibl corresp="http://zotero.org/groups/358366/items/PEN2K2AG"><seg type="journalArticle"><!-- attributes from original bibl--></seg><ptr target="bm:Grebaut1935Formules"/><title level="a">Deux formules de bénédicité</title><title level="j">Aethiopica</title><author><t:forename xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Sylvain</t:forename><t:surname xmlns:t="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0">Grébaut</t:surname></author><date>1935</date><biblScope unit="volume">3</biblScope><biblScope unit="issue">2</biblScope><biblScope unit="page">49-57</biblScope><citedRange unit="chapter">II</citedRange></bibl>. The witnesses of the
                         short version are numerous and show many deviations.</p>
            </abstract>
